context: The abbey was restored to the Benedictines under the Catholic <a0_0><b4_0><b5_0>Mary I of England<b5_0/><b4_0/><a0_0/>, but they were again ejected under <a1_0><b6_0><b7_0>Elizabeth I<b7_0/><b6_0/><a1_0/> in 1559. In 1560, Elizabeth re-established Westminster as a "Royal Peculiar" – a church of the Church of England responsible directly to the Sovereign, rather than to a diocesan bishop – and made it the <a2_0>Collegiate Church of St Peter<a2_0/> (that is, a non-cathedral church with an attached chapter of canons, headed by a dean.) <a3_0><b8_0>The last of Mary's abbots<b8_0/><a3_0/> was made the first dean.
